    title: 'The Future of Global Freight Logistics in 2025 and Beyond',
    excerpt: 'How emerging technologies and shifting trade routes are reshaping the logistics industry. From AI-driven supply chains to green shipping initiatives.',
    content: `<p>The global freight logistics industry is undergoing a massive transformation. With the rise of artificial intelligence, blockchain technology, and green shipping initiatives, the way goods move around the world is changing faster than ever.</p>
    <h3>AI-Powered Supply Chains</h3>
    <p>Artificial intelligence is revolutionizing supply chain management. Predictive analytics can now forecast demand with remarkable accuracy, allowing logistics companies to optimize routes, reduce waste, and improve delivery times. At WTL, we are investing heavily in AI-driven tools to provide our clients with real-time insights and smarter logistics solutions.</p>
    <h3>Green Shipping Initiatives</h3>
    <p>Environmental sustainability is no longer optional in the logistics industry. New regulations from the International Maritime Organization (IMO) are pushing shipping companies to reduce carbon emissions. WTL is committed to sustainable logistics, implementing fuel-efficient routing, electric vehicles for last-mile delivery, and carbon offset programs.</p>
    <h3>Shifting Trade Routes</h3>
    <p>Geopolitical changes and new trade agreements are creating new corridors for global trade. The African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA) is opening up unprecedented opportunities for intra-African trade, and WTL is positioned at the forefront of this transformation with our strong presence in Senegal and across West Africa.</p>
    <h3>Digital Documentation</h3>
    <p>Paper-based documentation is becoming a thing of the past. Electronic bills of lading, digital customs declarations, and blockchain-verified certificates of origin are streamlining international trade. WTL's digital platform ensures that all documentation is handled electronically, reducing delays and minimizing errors.</p>`,
